.:: Puzzle 3x5-Level-4-5::.
City: prague, rome, new-york, london, hannover
There 5 different types of food: orange, pumpkin, raspberry, spinach, cabbage
The people use 5 different means of transport: airplane, scooter, ship, snowmobile, train
 1. the person driving the scooter is the person traveling to hannover##1
 2. the person driving the train is on the left or right of the person traveling to new-york##3
 3. the person driving the ship is in an even position##4
 4. the person traveling to hannover is the person eating spinach##1
 5. the person driving the snowmobile is between the person driving the airplane and the person traveling to hannover##2
 6. the person traveling to rome is in the middle##1
 7. the person eating orange is on the left of the person eating pumpkin##1
 8. the person driving the airplane is on the right of the person eating raspberry##1
 9. the person eating cabbage is on the far right##1
10. the person eating raspberry is on the left of the person driving the airplane##1
11. the person traveling to london is the person eating cabbage##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1     |     2      |    3     |     4     |    5    |
| City   | hannover    | prague        | rome    | new-york      | london  |
| Food   | spinach | raspberry    | orange | pumpkin | cabbage |
| Transport     | scooter   | snowmobile | airplane | ship      | train   |

